======================================================================
SECTION 1: PERMANENT vs HAMILTONIAN PATH COUNT
======================================================================

For a tournament on n vertices:
  H(T) = number of Hamiltonian paths
  perm(A) = permanent of adjacency matrix
  perm(A) counts ALL directed path-covers (not just single paths)

Relation: H counts permutation matrices P with A[i][P(i)]=1
  where P is a single cycle... NO, H counts sequences.
  Actually: perm(A) = sum over ALL permutations sigma of prod A[i][sigma(i)]
  which counts permutation matrices ≤ A, i.e., directed 1-factors.

H counts Hamiltonian PATHS = directed walks visiting all vertices once.
These correspond to permutations sigma where (1,sigma(1),sigma^2(1),...)  is a path.
But perm(A) counts all perfect matchings in the bipartite double cover.

Let's compute both and compare:

--- p = 3 ---
  S=[1]: H=3, perm(A)=-1, perm/H=-0.3333
  S=[2]: H=3, perm(A)=-1, perm/H=-0.3333

--- p = 5 ---
  S=[1, 2]: H=15, perm(A)=-2, perm/H=-0.1333
  S=[1, 3]: H=15, perm(A)=-2, perm/H=-0.1333
  S=[2, 4]: H=15, perm(A)=-2, perm/H=-0.1333
  S=[3, 4]: H=15, perm(A)=-2, perm/H=-0.1333

--- p = 7 ---
  S=[1, 2, 3]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771
  S=[1, 2, 4]: H=189, perm(A)=-24, perm/H=-0.1270
  S=[1, 3, 5]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771
  S=[1, 4, 5]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771
  S=[2, 3, 6]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771
  S=[2, 4, 6]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771
  S=[3, 5, 6]: H=189, perm(A)=-24, perm/H=-0.1270
  S=[4, 5, 6]: H=175, perm(A)=-31, perm/H=-0.1771

======================================================================
SECTION 2: EIGENVALUE-PERMANENT CONNECTION
======================================================================

For a matrix with eigenvalues lambda_1,...,lambda_n:
  det(A) = prod lambda_i  (easy)
  perm(A) = ???  (hard — no clean eigenvalue formula)

But for CIRCULANT matrices, eigenvalues have special structure.
For circulant tournament on Z_p with connection set S:
  lambda_k = sum_{s in S} omega^{ks}
  A = sum_{s in S} P^s where P = permutation matrix of shift

Key: A = f(P) where f(x) = sum_{s in S} x^s
Eigenvalues: f(omega^k) for k=0,...,p-1

--- p = 7 ---
  S=[1, 2, 4]: H=189, prod|λ|=8.0000, Σ|λ|²=12.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=24.0000
  S=[3, 5, 6]: H=189, prod|λ|=8.0000, Σ|λ|²=12.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=24.0000
  S=[4, 5, 6]: H=175, prod|λ|=1.0000, Σ|λ|²=12.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=52.0000
  S=[1, 2, 3]: H=175, prod|λ|=1.0000, Σ|λ|²=12.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=52.0000
  Corr(H, prod|λ|) = 1.0000
  Corr(H, Σ|λ|⁴) = -1.0000

--- p = 11 ---
  S=[2, 6, 7, 8, 10]: H=95095, prod|λ|=243.0000, Σ|λ|²=30.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=90.0000
  S=[1, 3, 4, 5, 9]: H=95095, prod|λ|=243.0000, Σ|λ|²=30.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=90.0000
  S=[3, 6, 7, 9, 10]: H=93467, prod|λ|=23.0000, Σ|λ|²=30.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=178.0000
  S=[2, 3, 4, 5, 10]: H=92411, prod|λ|=23.0000, Σ|λ|²=30.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=134.0000
  Corr(H, prod|λ|) = 0.7519
  Corr(H, Σ|λ|⁴) = -0.0879

--- p = 13 ---
  S=[7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 12]: H=3711175, prod|λ|=1.0000, Σ|λ|²=42.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=602.0000
  S=[1, 2, 3, 7, 8, 9]: H=3711175, prod|λ|=1.0000, Σ|λ|²=42.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=602.0000
  S=[1, 4, 7, 8, 10, 11]: H=3711175, prod|λ|=1.0000, Σ|λ|²=42.0000, Σ|λ|⁴=602.0000
