======================================================================
SECTION 6: AM-GM AND SPECTRAL FLATNESS
======================================================================

By AM-GM: (prod |λ_k|^2)^{1/m} ≤ (1/m) Σ |λ_k|^2
with equality iff all |λ_k|^2 are equal (FLAT spectrum).

Since Σ|λ_k|^2 = p(p-1)/4 is CONSTANT (Parseval),
the product is maximized at flat spectrum.

But does max PRODUCT imply max H? Let's test.

--- p = 7 ---
  H=     189, prod|λ|²=       64.0000, AM-GM ratio=1.000000
  H=     189, prod|λ|²=       64.0000, AM-GM ratio=1.000000
  H=     175, prod|λ|²=        1.0000, AM-GM ratio=0.015625
  H=     175, prod|λ|²=        1.0000, AM-GM ratio=0.015625
  H=     175, prod|λ|²=        1.0000, AM-GM ratio=0.015625
  Corr(H, prod|λ|²) = 1.000000
  Corr(H, AM-GM ratio) = 1.000000
  Max H at index 0, max prod|λ|² at index 1
  SAME? NO

